{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Legislate to stop headlight flashing by cars with ultra bright LED headlights",
        "additional_details": "In the interests of road safety and driver comfort we believe this LED headlight flashing menace should be actively discouraged. As a happily retired former ADI (approved driving instructor) I previously encouraged students to momentarily dip down (i.e. switch from dipped headlights to sidelights for a moment). This signal to other road users is perfectly clear and no discomfort is caused by this \"come on\" or \"thank you\" signal.",
        "background": "Ultra bright LED headlights may be of benefit to drivers of these cars to the detriment of other road users, particularly at night time. Showing another driver a courtesy should not result in being stabbed in the eyes by LED headlights on full beam, thus instantly spoiling one\u2019s night time vision.",
